17/12/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The election-winning Liberal Democratic Party (PDL) and the Social Democratic Party (PSD) completed negotiations Tuesday (December 16th) on the structure of the new government. The cabinet will have a prime minister, 18 ministers, a deputy prime minister and a minister for relations with parliament. The justice ministry will be led by an independent expert to guarantee reforms continue, PSD leader Mircea Geoana said. Prime Minister-designate Emil Boc announced that the governance programme and the cabinet picks would likely be submitted to parliament Friday. (Adevarul, Gandul, Evenimentul Zilei - 17/12/08; Mediafax, Agerpres, Ziare - 16/12/08)
